### GET `/zalo-groups/account/:id`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `GET`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups/account/:id`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.findAllByZaloAccountId`

#### Description
Return paginated Zalo groups linked to a specific Zalo account. Each item has the shared group data plus the real `groupZaloId` stored on that account-group mapping.

Optional query **`group_name`**: when provided (non-empty after trim), only groups whose stored **`group_name`** contains that substring are returned, **case-insensitive** (SQL `ILIKE` / “contains” semantics). When omitted or blank, all linked groups are listed as before.

Optional query **`global_id`**: exact match on **`zalo_groups.global_id`** (not returned in items).

#### Request
- Params:
  - `id`: `string`, UUID of the target `zaloAccountId`
- Query:
  - `page`: `number`, optional, default `1`, minimum `1`
  - `limit`: `number`, optional, default `20`, minimum `1`
  - `group_name`: `string`, optional — substring filter on `zalo_groups.group_name` (case-insensitive contains); omit to skip filtering
  - `global_id`: `string`, optional — exact match on `zalo_groups.global_id`
- Body: none

#### Response

```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001",
      "groupName": "Marketing Team",
      "originName": "Marketing Team",
      "groupZaloId": "1234567890123456789",
      "isUpdateName": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-04-15T08:20:00.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-15T08:20:00.000Z",
      "_count": {
        "accountMaps": 3,
        "messages": 18
      }
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 20,
    "total": 1,
    "totalPages": 1
  }
}
```

#### Error cases
- `400`: invalid UUID or pagination query
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not allowed
- `404`: Zalo account not found
- `500`: unexpected server error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Roles: authenticated `ADMIN` or `USER`

### POST `/zalo-groups`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `POST`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.create`

#### Description
Create a new Zalo group record directly in the database.

Note: `group_zalo_id` is the Zalo group identifier received from a specific account context. It is stored on the account-group mapping model, not as a global field on `ZaloGroup`.

On create, `originName` is set once to the trimmed `group_name` and is **not** changed by later updates to `group_name` (see PUT).

#### Request
- Params: none
- Query: none
- Body:
  - `group_name`: `string`, required, minimum length `1`
  - `group_zalo_id`: `string`, required, minimum length `1`
  - `global_id`: `string`, optional — Zalo group global id; **unique when set**; not returned in responses

Example request:

```json
{
  "group_name": "Marketing Team",
  "group_zalo_id": "1234567890123456789",
  "global_id": "EPHPVTP4JNKHS9M7F4QP0UK2I8978C00"
}
```

#### Response

```json
{
  "id": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001",
  "groupName": "Marketing Team",
  "originName": "Marketing Team",
  "isUpdateName": false,
  "createdAt": "2026-04-15T08:20:00.000Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-15T08:20:00.000Z"
}
```

#### Error cases
- `400`: validation error
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not `ADMIN`
- `409`: group already exists in database
- `500`: unexpected server error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Required role: `ADMIN`

### POST `/zalo-groups/bulk/:id`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `POST`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups/bulk/:id`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.createMultiple`

#### Description
Create multiple Zalo groups in one request for a specific Zalo account. The `:id` route parameter is the target `zaloAccountId`.

For each new group:
- one row is created in `ZaloGroup`
- one row is created in `ZaloAccountGroup` to map that group to the provided Zalo account
- the target account `groupCount` is recalculated after the transaction

`group_zalo_id` here is the Zalo group identifier returned in the context of the provided account mapping. By default, existing mappings for this account are **skipped** (no second insert). Optional body field `mode` changes that (see below).

For each **new** `ZaloGroup` row, `originName` is set to the trimmed `group_name` at insert time. With default behavior, later calls do not change `originName` for rows that already exist for this account.

- `mode` (optional): when exactly **`"update origin name"`**, each `group_zalo_id` that already exists for this account no longer counts as “skipped”: the linked `ZaloGroup.originName` is set to the trimmed `group_name` from the request. New `group_zalo_id` values are still inserted as usual. Other values for `mode` are rejected (validation).

#### Request
- Params:
  - `id`: `string`, UUID of the target `zaloAccountId`
- Query: none
- Body:
  - `groups`: `Array<{ group_name: string; group_zalo_id: string; global_id?: string }>` required, minimum `1` item
  - `mode`: `string`, optional — must be `"update origin name"` when present

Example request:

```json
{
  "groups": [
    {
      "group_name": "Marketing Team",
      "group_zalo_id": "1234567890123456789",
      "global_id": "EPHPVTP4JNKHS9M7F4QP0UK2I8978C00"
    },
    {
      "group_name": "Sales Team",
      "group_zalo_id": "2234567890123456789"
    }
  ]
}
```

With `"mode": "update origin name"` at the top level of the body (next to `groups`), existing `group_zalo_id` entries update `originName` instead of appearing under `skipped.existingGroupZaloIds`.

#### Response

- `created`: new `ZaloGroup` rows (same shape as before).
- `updatedOriginName`: groups whose `originName` was updated (empty array unless `mode` is `"update origin name"`).
- `skipped.existingGroupZaloIds`: empty when `mode` is `"update origin name"` and every requested existing id was handled as an update; otherwise lists `group_zalo_id` values that were skipped because they already exist.

```json
{
  "created": [
    {
      "id": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001",
      "groupName": "Marketing Team",
      "originName": "Marketing Team",
      "isUpdateName": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-04-16T08:20:00.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-16T08:20:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "updatedOriginName": [],
  "skipped": {
    "existingGroupZaloIds": [
      "2234567890123456789"
    ],
    "duplicateInputGroupZaloIds": []
  },
  "summary": {
    "requested": 2,
    "uniqueRequested": 2,
    "created": 1,
    "updatedOriginName": 0,
    "skippedExisting": 1,
    "skippedDuplicateInput": 0
  }
}
```

#### Error cases
- `400`: validation error
- `400`: duplicate `group_zalo_id` values in the same request are skipped, not inserted twice
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not allowed
- `404`: Zalo account not found
- `500`: unexpected server error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Roles: authenticated `ADMIN` or `USER`

### POST `/zalo-groups/invite-member`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `POST`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups/invite-member`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.inviteMemberToGroup`

#### Description
Invite a **child** Zalo user into a Zalo group using the **master** account’s stored login session. The endpoint **only** calls Zalo (`findUser` + `addUserToGroup`); it does **not** create or update `zalo_account_groups` rows. Use **`ZaloGroup.global_id`** (Zalo’s unique group id, identical for master and child views) to identify the group in your app and in this API when possible.

Behavior:
1. Resolves the **`ZaloAccountGroup`** row for **`masterZaloAccountId`** (must be `isMaster = true`) to obtain **`groupZaloId`** for zca-js:
   - If **`globalId`** is set: find **`ZaloGroup`** by **`zalo_groups.global_id`**, then the mapping **master + that `group_id`**. (When `globalId` is sent, **`groupId` / `groupName` are ignored** for lookup.)
   - Else if **`groupId`** (internal `ZaloGroup.id` UUID) is set: same as before; **`groupName` is not used for lookup**; the **first** mapping by **`joinedAt` ascending** wins if duplicates.
   - Else **`groupName`** is required: find by **`ZaloGroup.groupName`** scoped to this master; **first** by **`joinedAt` ascending** wins.
2. Resolves the invitee’s **phone** from `phoneNumber` and/or the child row (`childZaloAccountId`).
3. On the **master** `sessionId`, calls Zalo `findUser(phone)` for the **friend-graph `uid`**, then **`addUserToGroup(uid, groupZaloId)`** (master’s grid id from the mapping row — Zalo’s API still uses the per-device grid id for the call, while **`globalId`** in our DB is the stable identifier for the group).

**Frontend requirements**
- `sessionId`: latest `zalo_login_sessions.id` for the **master** (same pattern as `GET /zalo/actions/groups?sessionId=...`).
- Master must be **Zalo friends** with the invitee and have permission to add members to that group (Zalo-side rules).
- If `childZaloAccountId` is sent, that account must exist in `zalo_account_relations` as a **child** of `masterZaloAccountId` (used to resolve `phone` only).
- After a **successful** Zalo invite, if **`childZaloAccountId`** is set, the server attempts to **enqueue a background child group scan** (same pipeline as `POST /zalo-accounts/:id/child-group-scan`: `getAllGroups` + batched `getGroupInfo`, Redis cache, `zalo_account_groups` mapping by `globalId`). The child’s **`ZaloAccount.status`** becomes **`INACTIVE`** for the duration of that work (and is set back to **`ACTIVE`** when the last chunk finishes, or on error). The client should read **`status`** from account payloads (e.g. list/detail) to hide repeat actions (e.g. “quét nhóm” / invite-driven sync) while **`INACTIVE`**.

#### Request
- Params: none
- Query: none
- Body:
  - `globalId`: `string`, optional, non-empty after trim — Zalo **group** global id (`zalo_groups.global_id`); **preferred**; when present, **`groupId` / `groupName` are ignored** for lookup
  - `groupId`: `string`, optional, UUID — internal `ZaloGroup.id`; when present (and `globalId` omitted), **ignores `groupName`**
  - `groupName`: `string`, required if neither `globalId` nor `groupId` is sent — must match a group linked to **`masterZaloAccountId`**
  - `sessionId`: `string`, UUID — master `zalo_login_sessions.id`
  - `masterZaloAccountId`: `string`, UUID — master `zalo_accounts.id` (`isMaster` must be `true`)
  - `phoneNumber`: `string`, optional, minimum length `5` — used for `findUser` on the master session; may be omitted if `childZaloAccountId` is provided and that row has `phone`
  - `childZaloAccountId`: `string`, optional, UUID — child account; when present, must be linked to the master via `zalo_account_relations`; supplies `phone` when `phoneNumber` is omitted

Example request:

```json
{
  "groupName": "Nhóm bán hàng A",
  "sessionId": "e2c52ab6-5134-4f9c-9968-3e8b430094aa",
  "masterZaloAccountId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91"
}
```

Example with explicit phone:

```json
{
  "groupName": "Nhóm bán hàng A",
  "sessionId": "e2c52ab6-5134-4f9c-9968-3e8b430094aa",
  "masterZaloAccountId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "phoneNumber": "0914405474",
  "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91"
}
```

Example with internal group UUID (no `groupName` needed for lookup):

```json
{
  "groupId": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001",
  "sessionId": "e2c52ab6-5134-4f9c-9968-3e8b430094aa",
  "masterZaloAccountId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91"
}
```

Example with **`globalId`** (preferred when `zalo_groups.global_id` is set):

```json
{
  "globalId": "EPHPVTP4JNKHS9M7F4QP0UK2I8978C00",
  "sessionId": "e2c52ab6-5134-4f9c-9968-3e8b430094aa",
  "masterZaloAccountId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91"
}
```

#### Response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "masterGroupZaloId": "4722820980206948279",
  "inviteUid": "4546690961257603620",
  "findUser": {
    "display_name": "Đào Văn Phương",
    "globalId": "FJQ9QJLN50FORDFDT87QJPEMDV420BO0"
  },
  "zalo": {
    "errorMembers": [],
    "error_data": {}
  }
}
```

(`zalo` shape follows zca-js `addUserToGroup` response. This route does **not** create or update database rows.)

#### Error cases
- `400`: validation error; no way to identify the group (`globalId` / `groupId` / `groupName`); master not `isMaster`; child is master; child not linked to master; could not resolve phone; Zalo `addUserToGroup` returned non-empty `errorMembers` / `error_data`; Zalo API error (e.g. not friends, not admin, invalid params) — message may be prefixed with `[code]`
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not allowed
- `404`: master account not found; child account not found; **`ZaloGroup` not found** (unknown `groupId` or unknown **`global_id`**); no `ZaloAccountGroup` row for **this master** and the resolved group; no group for **name** (legacy lookup)
- `500`: failed to restore Zalo client from session credentials; unexpected error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Roles: authenticated `ADMIN` or `USER`

### POST `/zalo-groups/remove-member`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `POST`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups/remove-member`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.removeMemberFromGroup`

#### Description
Remove a Zalo user from a group using the **master** session, mirroring **`POST /zalo-groups/invite-member`** but calling Zalo **`removeUserFromGroup(memberUid, groupZaloId)`** instead of `addUserToGroup`.

Same group resolution as invite: prefer **`globalId`**, else **`groupId`**, else **`groupName`**, plus `masterZaloAccountId`. Same member resolution. The **`groupZaloId`** for Zalo is from the master’s **`zalo_account_groups`** row.

After a successful remove (`errorMembers` empty), if **`childZaloAccountId`** is set, the API **deletes** the child’s **`zalo_account_groups`** row for that internal `group_id` (if present) and refreshes the child’s **`groupCount`**.

#### Request
- Params: none
- Query: none
- Body: same fields as **`POST /zalo-groups/invite-member`**, including optional **`globalId`**, plus `groupId`, `groupName`, `sessionId`, `masterZaloAccountId`, `phoneNumber`, `childZaloAccountId`.

Example:

```json
{
  "groupName": "Nhóm bán hàng A",
  "sessionId": "e2c52ab6-5134-4f9c-9968-3e8b430094aa",
  "masterZaloAccountId": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91"
}
```

#### Response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "masterGroupZaloId": "4722820980206948279",
  "removedMemberUid": "4546690961257603620",
  "findUser": {
    "display_name": "Đào Văn Phương",
    "globalId": "FJQ9QJLN50FORDFDT87QJPEMDV420BO0"
  },
  "zalo": {
    "errorMembers": []
  },
  "dbSync": {
    "persisted": true,
    "childZaloAccountId": "fd87478e-14ae-46b5-8aec-e3800b800c91",
    "groupId": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001"
  }
}
```

(`zalo` shape follows zca-js `removeUserFromGroup`. If `childZaloAccountId` is omitted, `dbSync.persisted` is `false` and `dbSync.reason` explains the skip.)

#### Error cases
- `400`: validation error; same account/relation/phone cases as invite-member; Zalo `removeUserFromGroup` returned non-empty `errorMembers`; Zalo API error
- `401` / `403` / `404` / `500`: same categories as **invite-member** (session restore, not found, etc.)

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Roles: authenticated `ADMIN` or `USER`

### PUT `/zalo-groups/:id`
#### Endpoint
- Method: `PUT`
- Full path: `/zalo-groups/:id`
- Function: `ZaloGroupsController.update`

#### Description
Update a stored Zalo group directly in the database and mark `isUpdateName` as `true`.

Note: updating this endpoint changes only the shared `ZaloGroup` record. `group_zalo_id` remains account-specific data on `ZaloAccountGroup`.

`originName` is **not** modified by this endpoint; it stays as set on create.

#### Request
- Params:
  - `id`: `string`, UUID
- Query: none
- Body:
  - `group_name`: `string`, required, minimum length `1`
  - `group_zalo_id`: `string`, required, minimum length `1`
  - `global_id`: `string`, optional — Zalo group global id (unique when set); stored for server-side filtering only; **not** included in JSON responses

Example request:

```json
{
  "group_name": "Marketing Team Renamed",
  "group_zalo_id": "1234567890123456789",
  "global_id": "EPHPVTP4JNKHS9M7F4QP0UK2I8978C00"
}
```

#### Response

```json
{
  "id": "5d6a8d48-b45c-43d8-9b0d-5cc3bd110001",
  "groupName": "Marketing Team Renamed",
  "originName": "Marketing Team",
  "isUpdateName": true,
  "createdAt": "2026-04-15T08:20:00.000Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-15T08:25:00.000Z"
}
```

#### Error cases
- `400`: invalid UUID or body validation error
- `401`: missing/invalid JWT
- `403`: role is not `ADMIN`
- `404`: group record not found
- `409`: another record already uses the same Zalo group
- `500`: unexpected server error

#### Authentication
- JWT required
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`
- Required role: `ADMIN`

